Ciba rights start trading at 100 Sfr . Rights for shares in Ciba Specialty Chemicals Holding Inc , being spun off from Novartis , started trading on the Swiss Exchange at 100 Swiss francs . A bank consortium has fixed a floor price of 64 francs per right , representing a share price of 74 francs per registered share , for the rights , which are being issued to Novartis shareholders in a one - for - one rights issue . The consortium will use the rights to buy shares for sale in a global offering with at least 300 million francs worth of shares . Share trading starts on March 13 . - - Zurich + 41 1 631 7340 
